article.description: — Jonathan Cisse scored 22 points and Incarnate Word beat Dartmouth 69-64 on Friday night.
article.headline: Incarnate Word wins 69-64 against Dartmouth
article.story: SAN ANTONIO -- — Jonathan Cisse scored 22 points and Incarnate Word beat Dartmouth 69-64 on Friday night. Cisse added seven rebounds for the Cardinals (3-3). Davante Dennis added 17 points, seven rebounds and five steals. Trey Miller scored 15 points. Brandon Mitchell-Day led the Big Green (1-4) in scoring, finishing with 14 points and six rebounds. Demilade Adelekun added nine points, 15 rebounds and three blocks for Dartmouth. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
